        default CommandHandleBuilder getChild(java.lang.String commandName)
        Attempts to find a subcommand by the specified name.
        Parameters:
        commandName - the name of the command. By default this is the name of the method or the name of the inner class. If the subcommand is an inner class and its name ends in "command", the name only includes the part preceding "command".
        Returns:
        The CommandHandleBuilder of the sub command.
        Throws:
        NoSuchCommandException - when the subcommand is not found

      • getDeclaringObject

        java.lang.Object getDeclaringObject()
        This method returns null if the command has been defined with a class or a supplier. If this command was defined with a Consumer or Object, it will return that object.
        Returns:
        the object supplied to create this command.

      • getDeclaringClass

        java.lang.Class getDeclaringClass()
        This command returns the enclosing class of this command.
        • If this command was defined by a Consumer, the Class of that consumer is returned.
        • If this command was defined by a Supplier, the Class of the result from that Supplier is returned.
        • If this command was defined by an Object, the Class of that Object is returned.
        • If this command was defined by a Class, then that Class is returned.
        • If this command is a sub-command defined by a Method, then the Class or Inner Class enclosing that Method is returned.
        Returns:
        a Class.

      • getDeclaringMethod

        java.lang.reflect.Method getDeclaringMethod()
        Returns the method that is used to invoke this command. If this command was defined with a Consumer, this returns null.
        Returns:
        a Method
